<p><ol>
<li><a href="https://github.com/kig/JSARToolKit">JSARToolKit</a> -- Javascript port of the Flash AR Toolkit.  I'm intrigued because the iPad2 has rear-facing camera and gyroscopes up the wazoo, and (of course) no Flash.  (via <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/shaver/status/43424165541314560">Mike Shaver on Twitter</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.androidpatterns.com/wiki">Android Patterns</a> -- set of design patterns for Android apps. (via <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/globalmoxie/status/43399954890362880">Josh Clark on Twitter</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://ofps.oreilly.com/titles/9781449398583/">Preview of Up and Running with Node.js</a> (O'Reilly) -- Tom Hughes-Croucher's new book in preview form. Just sorting out commenting now. (via <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/sh1mmer/status/43396775997997057">Tom on Twitter</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://tomafro.net/2011/03/hashblue-opens-for-business">#Blue Opens for Business</a> -- a web app that gets your text messages. You can reply, and there's an API to give other apps read/write access.  Signs the text message is finally becoming a consumer platform.</li>
</ol></p>

